erman}}</ref>\n{{8TeamBracket-NoSeeds\n| RD1=Quarterfinals\n| RD2=Semifinals\n| RD3=Final\n|RD1-team1='''Kota Sekifuda'''\n|RD1-team2=[[Tsutomu Oosugi]]\n|RD1-score1=Pin\n|RD1-score2=9:35\n|RD1-team3='''[[Kazuki Hashimoto]]'''\n|RD1-team4=Fuminori Abe\n|RD1-score3=Pin\n|RD1-score4=8:48\n|RD1-team5='''Yuya Aoki'''\n|RD1-team6=Kankuro Hoshino\n|RD1-score5=Pin\n|RD1-score6=9:04\n|RD1-team7='''[[Tatsuhito Senga|Hercules Senga]]*'''\n|RD1-team8=[[Tatsuhiko Yoshino]]\n|RD1-score7=Pin\n|RD1-score8=2:17\n|RD2-team1=Kota Sekifuda\n|RD2-team2='''Kazuki Hashimoto'''\n|RD2-score1=Pin\n|RD2-score2=6:57\n|RD2-team3=Yuya Aoki\n|RD2-team4='''Banana Senga'''\n|RD2-score3=Pin\n|RD2-score4=5:49\n|RD3-team1='''Kazuki Hashimoto'''\n|RD3-team2=Banana Senga\n|RD3-score1=Pin\n|RD3-score2=11:57\n}}\n*Hercules Senga changed his ring name to Banana Senga in the semi-final round.\n\n===6-Man Sacred Ground City of Forest Sendai Tournament===\nThe '''6-Man Sacred Ground City of Forest Sendai Tournament''' was a six-man tag team tournament, in which the [[Yokohama Shopping Street 6-Man Tag Team Championship]] was defended. The tournament was held on August 5, 2018. The defending champions [[Abdullah Kobayashi]], [[Ryuji Ito]] and [[Jaki Numazawa]] lost the titles to Masaya Takahashi, Takayuki Ueki and Toshiyuki Sakuda, who would successfully defend the titles in the final round to win the tournament.\n<center>{{4TeamBracket\n| RD1= Semifinals\n| RD2= Finals\n| RD1-seed1=\n| RD1-seed2=\n| RD1-seed3=\n| RD1-seed4=\n| RD2-seed1=\n| RD2-seed2=\n| RD1-team1='''[[Ryota Hama]], [[Yasufumi Nakanoue]] and Yoshihisa Uto'''\n| RD1-team2=[[Daisuke Sekimoto]], Hideyoshi Kamitani and [[Daichi Hashimoto]]\n| RD1-team3=[[Abdullah Kobayashi]], [[Ryuji Ito]] and [[Jaki Numazawa]] (c)\n| RD1-team4='''Masaya Takahashi, Takayuki Ueki and Toshiyuki Sakuda'''\n| RD2-team1=Ryota Hama, Yasufumi Nakanoue and Yoshihisa Uto\n| RD2-team2='''Masaya Takahashi, Takayuki Ueki and Toshiyuki Sakuda (c)'''\n}}\n</center>\n\n==Saikyo Tag League==\n{{main|Saikyo Tag League}}\nSaikyo Tag League is a professional wrestling round-robin hardcore tag team tournament annually held since 1999.\n\n===Dates and venues of finals===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Event\n!Date\n!City\n!Venue\n!Winner\n|-\n|[[Saikyo Tag League#1999|1999]]\n|November 8, 1999\n|[[Sapporo]], [[Hokkaido]]\n|Teisen Hall\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Tomoaki Honma]] and [[Ryuji Yamakawa]]\n|-\n|[[Saikyo Tag League#2000|2000]]\n|October 30, 2000\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Tokyo]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Korakuen Hall]]\n|-\n|[[Saikyo Tag League#2001|2001]]\n|September 23, 2001\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Men's Teioh]] and [[Daisuke Sekimoto]]\n|-\n|[[Saikyo Tag League#2002|2002]]\n|October 31, 2002\n|[[Yokohama]], [[Kanagawa Prefecture|Kanagawa]]\n|[[Yokohama Red Brick Warehouse]]\n|-\n|[[Saikyo Tag League#2003|2003]]\n|November 8, 2003\n|rowspan=\"9\"|Tokyo\n|rowspan=\"9\"|Korakuen Hall\n|Daikokubo Benkei and [[Abdullah Kobayashi]]\n|-\n|[[Saikyo Tag League#2009|2009]]\n|May 28, 2009\n|[[Masashi Takeda (wrestler)|Masashi Takeda]] and [[Isami Kodaka]]\n|-\n|[[Saikyo Tag League#2011|2011]]\n|November 22, 2011\n|[[Daisuke Sekimoto]] and [[Yuji Okabayashi]]\n|-\n|[[Saikyo Tag League#2012|2012]]\n|November 24, 2012\n|rowspan=\"3\"|Isami Kodaka and [[Yuko Miyamoto]]\n|-\n|[[Saikyo Tag League#2013|2013]]\n|November 22, 2013\n|-\n|[[Saikyo Tag League#2014|2014]]\n|November 21, 2014\n|-\n|[[Saikyo Tag League#2015|2015]]\n|October 29, 2015\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Daisuke Sekimoto and Yuji Okabayashi\n|-\n|[[Saikyo Tag League#2016|2016]]\n|October 31, 2016\n|-\n|[[Saikyo Tag League#2017|2017]]\n|October 15, 2017\n|[[Daichi Hashimoto]] and Hideyoshi Kamitani\n|}\n\n==Ikkitousen Deathmatch Survivor==\n{{main|Ikkitousen Deathmatch Survivor}}\nIkkitousen Deathmatch Survivor is an annual professional wrestling round-robin hardcore tournament to determine the best wrestler of BJW's deathmatch division.\n\n===Dates and venues of finals===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Event\n!Date\n!City\n!Ve