p Tournament (1998)===\nThe '''BJW Junior Heavyweight Championship Tournament''' was an eight-man single-elimination tournament conducted on March 2, 1998 to crown the inaugural [[BJW Junior Heavyweight Championship (1998\u20132002)|BJW Junior Heavyweight Champion]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Big Japan Junior Heavyweight Title Tournament 1998 |url=http://prowrestlinghistory.com/supercards/japan/garbage/bjw/title.html#junior |publisher=Pro Wrestling History |accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref>\n{{8TeamBracket-NoSeeds\n| RD1=Quarterfinals\n| RD2=Semifinals\n| RD3=Final\n| RD1-team1 = '''[[Yoshihiro Tajiri]]'''\n| RD1-team2 = [[Gran Naniwa]]\n| RD1-score1 = Pin\n| RD1-score2 =\n| RD1-team3 = '''[[Minoru Tanaka (wrestler)|Minoru Tanaka]]'''\n| RD1-team4 = [[Minoru Fujita]]\n| RD1-score3 = Pin\n| RD1-score4 = \n| RD1-team5 = '''[[Ryuji Yamakawa]]'''\n| RD1-team6 = [[Masayoshi Motegi]]\n| RD1-score5 = Pin\n| RD1-score6 = \n| RD1-team7 = '''[[Gedo (wrestler)|Gedo]]'''\n| RD1-team8 = [[Tomoaki Honma]]\n| RD1-score7 = Pin\n| RD1-score8 = \n| RD2-team1 = '''Yoshihiro Tajiri'''\n| RD2-team2 = Minoru Tanaka\n| RD2-score1 = Pin\n| RD2-score2 = \n| RD2-team3 = Ryuji Yamakawa\n| RD2-team4 = '''Gedo'''\n| RD2-score3 = Pin\n| RD2-score4 = \n| RD3-team1 = '''Yoshihiro Tajiri'''\n| RD3-team2 = Gedo\n| RD3-score1 = Pin\n| RD3-score2 = \n}}\n\n===BJW Deathmatch Heavyweight Championship Tournament (1998)===\nThe '''BJW Deathmatch Heavyweight Championship Tournament''' was held to crown the inaugural [[BJW Deathmatch Heavyweight Championship|BJW Deathmatch Heavyweight Champion]] from June 8 to August 9, 1998.<ref>{{cite web |title=Big Japan Death Match Title Tournament 1998 |url=http://prowrestlinghistory.com/supercards/japan/garbage/bjw/title.html#death |publisher=Pro Wrestling History |accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref>\n{{8TeamBracket-NoSeeds\n| RD1=Quarterfinals\n| RD2=Semifinals\n| RD3=Final\n| RD1-team1 = '''[[Mitsuhiro Matsunaga]]'''\n| RD1-team2 = Jason the Terrible\n| RD1-score1 =