04|url=http://prowrestlinghistory.com/supercards/japan/garbage/bjw/sixtag.html#2004|publisher=Pro Wrestling History |accessdate=24 September 2018}}</ref>\n<center>\n{{3RoundBracket-Byesnoseeds\n|RD1-Quarterfinals\n|RD2-Semifinals\n|RD3-Final\n|RD1-team1='''[[Kengo Mashimo]], Manabu Hara and [[Shiori Asahi]]'''\n|RD1-team2=Kudo, Daichi Kakimoto and TA*KU\n|RD1-team3='''[[Harashima|Hero!]], [[Jaki Numazawa]] and Super-X'''\n|RD1-team4=Kunio Toshima, Katsumasa Inoue and [[Mineo Fujita]]\n|RD1-team7='''[[Daisuke Sekimoto]], Futoshi Miwa and Kyosuke Sasaki'''\n|RD1-team8=Kazuhiro Tamura, Masanori Ishikura and [[Yuji Hino]]\n|RD2-team1=Kengo Mashimo, Manabu Hara and Shiori Asahi\n|RD2-team2='''Hero!, Jaki Numazawa and Super-X'''\n|RD2-team3='''Daisuke Sekimoto, Futoshi Miwa and Kyosuke Sasaki'''\n|RD2-team4=[[Shuji Ishikawa]], Hajime Moriyama and Kent\n|RD3-team1='''Hero!, Jaki Numazawa and Super-X'''\n|RD3-team2=Daisuke Sekimoto, Futoshi Miwa and Kyosuke Sasaki\n}}\n</center>\n\n===Number 1 of Japan Tournament===\nThe '''Number 1 of Japan Tournament''' was held on September 5, 2004.<ref>{{cite web |title=Number 1 of Japan Tournament 2004 |url=http://prowrestlinghistory.com/supercards/japan/garbage/bjw/misc.html#number |publisher=Pro Wrestling History |accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref>\n{{3RoundBracket-Byesnoseeds\n|RD1-team3=[[Abdullah Kobayashi]]\n|RD1-team4='''[[Jaki Numazawa]]'''\n|RD1-team5='''Katsumasa Inoue'''\n|RD1-team6=[[Shadow WX]]\n|RD1-team7=\n|RD1-team8=\n|RD2-team1=[[Ryuji Yamakawa]]\n|RD2-team2='''Jaki  Numazawa'''\n|RD2-team3=Katsumasa Inoue\n|RD2-team4='''[[Daisuke Sekimoto]]'''\n|RD3-team1=Jaki  Numazawa\n|RD3-team2='''Daisuke Sekimoto'''\n|RD1-score3=Pin\n|RD1-score4=11:05\n|RD1-score5=DQ\n|RD1-score6=9:08\n|RD2-score1=Pin\n|RD2-score3=Pin\n|RD3-score1=Pin\n|RD2-score2=7:47\n|RD2-score4=8:24\n|RD3-score2=7:13\n}}\n\n===New Generation Battle Tournament===\nThe '''New Generation Battle Tournament''' was a tournament held on January 9, 2005.<ref>{{cite web |title=New Generation Battle Tournament 2005 |url=http://prowrestlinghistory.com/supercards/japan/garbage/bjw/misc.html#generation |publisher=Pro Wrestling History |accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref>\n{{8TeamBracket-NoSeeds\n| RD1=Quarterfinals\n| RD2=Semifinals\n| RD3=Final\n| RD1-team1 = '''[[Daisuke Sekimoto]]'''\n| RD1-team2 = Kunio Toshima\n| RD1-score1 = Pin\n| RD1-score2 = 10:02\n| RD1-team3 = Masanori Ishikura\n| RD1-team4 = '''[[Mineo Fujita]]'''\n| RD1-score3 = Pin\n| RD1-score4 = 6:12\n| RD1-team5 = '''Kyosuke Sasaki'''\n| RD1-team6 = [[Jaki Numazawa]]\n| RD1-score5 = Pin\n| RD1-score6 = 4:37\n| RD1-team7 = Manabu Hara\n| RD1-team8 = '''[[Harashima|Hero!]]'''\n| RD1-score7 = Pin\n| RD1-score8 = 5:32\n| RD2-team1 = '''Daisuke Sekimoto'''\n| RD2-team2 = Mineo Fujita\n| RD2-score1 = Pin\n| RD2-score2 = 6:12\n| RD2-team3 = Kyosuke Sasaki\n| RD2-team4 = '''Hero!'''\n| RD2-score3 = Pin\n| RD2-score4 = 12:01\n| RD3-team1 = '''Daisuke Sekimoto'''\n| RD3-team2 = Hero!\n| RD3-score1 = Pin\n| RD3-score2 = 12:32\n}}\n\n===Dainichi Dash===\nThe '''Dainichi Dash''' was a tournament held on July 1, 2009.<ref>{{cite web |title=D-Dash Tournament|url=https://www.wrestlingdata.com/index.php?befehl=turniere&liga=25&kategorie=201&turnier=1075|work=Wrestling Data |accessdate=24 September 2018|language=German}}</ref>\n{{4RoundBracket-Byes\n|RD1-team01='''Takuma Obe'''\n|RD1-team02=Ryuichi Kawakami\n|RD1-team05='''[[Daisuke Sasaki]]'''\n|RD1-team06=Atsushi Ohashi\n|RD1-team09='''Shigehiro Irie'''\n|RD1-team10=Satoshi Kajiwara\n|RD1-team13='''Shinya Ishikawa'''\n|RD1-team14=Daisuke Masaoka\n|RD2-team01=Takuma Obe\n|RD2-team02='''[[Masashi Takeda (wrestler)|Masashi Takeda]]'''\n|RD2-team05=Shigehiro Irie\n|RD2-team06='''[[Yuji Okabayashi]]'''\n|RD2-team03='''Daisuke Sasaki'''\n|RD2-team04=BYE\n|RD2-team07='''Shinya Ishikawa'''\n|RD2-team08=BYE\n|RD3-team01=Daisuke Sasaki\n|RD3-team02='''Masashi Takeda'''\n|RD3-team03=Yuji Okabayashi\n|RD3-team04='''Shinya Ishikawa'''\n|RD4-